.TH "adj_for_padding" 9 "adj_for_padding" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
adj_for_padding \- adjust overlap to account for padding.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned char *" adj_for_padding
.BI "(unsigned char *buf_b "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *buf_a "  ","
.BI "size_t len_a "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf_b" 12
second buffer
.IP "buf_a" 12
first buffer
.IP "len_a" 12
size of first buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fIbuf_a\fP might have up to 7 bytes of padding appended. Adjust the overlap
accordingly.
.SH "RETURN"
A pointer into \fIbuf_b\fP from where non-overlapped data starts
